00:21:24,830 --> 00:21:27,370
I'm freaking tired
because of that bastard.

263
00:21:27,460 --> 00:21:30,290
I was dying to talk. That asshole.

264
00:21:30,880 --> 00:21:33,920
My head hurts from staring him down
so hard.

265
00:21:35,170 --> 00:21:37,510
Does anyone have anything for headaches?
Let me have one.

266
00:21:37,590 --> 00:21:38,420
Thanks.

267
00:21:38,720 --> 00:21:40,510
Hang in there until the warden returns.

268
00:21:41,090 --> 00:21:42,760
I'm really okay.

269
00:21:44,260 --> 00:21:45,890
I'll protect myself.

270
00:21:57,650 --> 00:21:59,820
Crony isn't here right now.

271
00:22:09,750 --> 00:22:11,620
It became a habit after one night.

272
00:22:12,790 --> 00:22:14,380
I got confused too.

273
00:22:15,630 --> 00:22:17,590
I didn't sleep a wink last night.

274
00:22:17,800 --> 00:22:20,760
Who did? I didn't sleep a wink either.

275
00:22:21,720 --> 00:22:24,180
How long do we have to live like this?

276
00:23:35,960 --> 00:23:37,250
What a joke.

277
00:23:42,340 --> 00:23:43,340
Min-chul.

278
00:23:44,220 --> 00:23:46,260
Must we really go this far?

279
00:23:46,340 --> 00:23:47,850
Didn't you see Crony's eyes?

280
00:23:48,140 --> 00:23:49,260
His eyes glazed over.

281
00:23:50,770 --> 00:23:53,890
He's on the brink of doing something.

282
00:23:55,600 --> 00:23:58,480
We'll protect Je-hyeok. Got it?

283
00:23:59,650 --> 00:24:02,110
Okay. It's just a few days.

284
00:24:03,030 --> 00:24:03,860
Oh, right.

285
00:24:04,780 --> 00:24:08,700
How is your retrial petition going?
Did you submit it yet?

286
00:24:09,120 --> 00:24:11,830
Not yet. My brother is preparing
the documents now.

287
00:24:12,410 --> 00:24:13,290
Soon.

288
00:24:14,160 --> 00:24:16,210
We'll submit the petition soon.

289
00:24:16,290 --> 00:24:17,750
It'll go well.

290
00:24:18,080 --> 00:24:18,920
Don't worry.

291
00:24:24,510 --> 00:24:27,930
A picture of Private Park's watch
stopped at 1:55 a.m.

292
00:24:28,010 --> 00:24:31,720
This one photo made Jung-min and me
come this far.

293
00:24:31,810 --> 00:24:33,810
NIGHT DUTY LOG
SEPTEMBER 20, 2016

294
00:24:34,100 --> 00:24:35,060
PRIVATE JUN-YEONG PARK

295
00:24:35,140 --> 00:24:38,520
We have the night duty log
with Private Park's name on it,

296
00:24:39,440 --> 00:24:40,980
and now, an eye witness.

297
00:24:43,530 --> 00:24:44,780
We're set now, right?

298
00:24:45,490 --> 00:24:47,950
Let's request a retrial right away.

299
00:24:49,450 --> 00:24:52,910
Our attorney, Mr. Kang, is very cautious.

300
00:24:52,990 --> 00:24:53,870
Sorry?

301
00:24:54,700 --> 00:24:58,000
Okay, we have our bullets ready to go.

302
00:24:58,120 --> 00:25:00,750
Now, we have to report Sergeant Oh.

303
00:25:01,630 --> 00:25:04,550
The most important thing for the retrial

304
00:25:04,630 --> 00:25:07,680
is to prove Sergeant Oh committed perjury.

305
00:25:09,340 --> 00:25:11,680
That means we need more soldiers

306
00:25:11,760 --> 00:25:14,970
to testify that they witnessed
what actually happened.

307
00:25:15,060 --> 00:25:17,100
That makes our case stronger.

308
00:25:17,190 --> 00:25:19,650
We need that to get the petition
for retrial granted.

309
00:25:22,110 --> 00:25:25,820
Then I'll meet with the soldiers
and talk to them.

310
00:25:26,940 --> 00:25:27,950
If they won't agree,

311
00:25:28,990 --> 00:25:30,320
I'll threaten them or something.

312
00:25:30,740 --> 00:25:33,910
I'm sure Corporal Choi
and Corporal Lim will listen.

313
00:25:33,990 --> 00:25:35,540
That would be great.

314
00:25:36,540 --> 00:25:39,250
We need to gather
anything we can right now. Why?

315
00:25:39,830 --> 00:25:42,710
Because Sergeant Oh's side
is on the move too.

316
00:25:43,710 --> 00:25:45,090
<i>Next on the news.</i>

317
00:25:45,210 --> 00:25:46,960
And at least because of that,

318
00:25:47,260 --> 00:25:49,720
it'll be bad if the case
gains attention again.

319
00:25:49,800 --> 00:25:51,050
<i>This morning,</i>

320
00:25:51,140 --> 00:25:53,800
<i>Senator Tae-gu Oh announced
his candidacy for a fourth term.</i>

321
00:25:54,600 --> 00:25:58,180
<i>He was a member
of the National Defense Committee</i>

322
00:25:58,270 --> 00:26:02,810
<i>and led many movements
such as reviving commercial regions.</i>

323
00:26:03,400 --> 00:26:07,110
<i>Senator Oh came in first
in a recent survey by a large margin,</i>

324
00:26:07,190 --> 00:26:10,110
<i>and is favored to win the election.</i>

325
00:26:10,200 --> 00:26:13,280
He has a lot of money and has
many connections in the legal world.

326
00:26:13,780 --> 00:26:15,700
He'll have an impressive legal team.

327
00:26:16,290 --> 00:26:17,160
Hey.

328
00:26:17,660 --> 00:26:19,290
Your firm is huge too.

329
00:26:19,370 --> 00:26:23,080
That's right. Of course. Trust me.

330
00:26:23,170 --> 00:26:25,800
Don't worry. We will win, no matter what.

331
00:26:36,760 --> 00:26:37,890
Bro. Just a minute.

332
00:26:44,810 --> 00:26:46,520
Ice cappuccino.

333
00:26:48,690 --> 00:26:50,400
How did you know? Thanks.

334
00:26:50,990 --> 00:26:52,820
I've been cleaning the office lately.

335
00:26:53,200 --> 00:26:54,820
I sneaked a peak in the computer.

336
00:26:54,910 --> 00:26:55,780
I hear you. Shit.

337
00:26:57,330 --> 00:27:00,910
I looked at your fan site
and read Gocheok Gunman's blog.

338
00:27:01,960 --> 00:27:04,460
It has 100,000 Q&A about Je-hyeok Kim.

339
00:27:06,250 --> 00:27:07,840
You should read it sometime.

340
00:27:08,000 --> 00:27:09,840
He knows everything about you.

341
00:27:10,260 --> 00:27:14,090
Joon-ho. Can't you ask Gocheok Gunman
to come visit?

342
00:27:14,180 --> 00:27:16,100
If you let him meet Je-hyeok,

343
00:27:16,180 --> 00:27:18,810
I'm sure he'll love you like a brother.

344
00:27:21,140 --> 00:27:22,310
No way.

345
00:27:22,390 --> 00:27:24,020
Seriously, meet him.

346
00:27:25,940 --> 00:27:28,650
You may know him already.
I didn't think of that.

347
00:27:28,730 --> 00:27:30,070
Yes, I'm sure he does.

348
00:27:31,110 --> 00:27:33,740
Diehard fans usually know each other.

349
00:27:34,740 --> 00:27:36,370
They're closer than most brothers.

350
00:27:37,330 --> 00:27:38,410
You bastard.

351
00:27:40,160 --> 00:27:42,370
You didn't take Crony out yet, right?

352
00:27:44,460 --> 00:27:48,210
Do you want to just sleep here?
I'm too worried. I can't take it.

353
00:27:49,670 --> 00:27:53,010
I'll protect myself.
Everyone must think I'm a weakling.

354
00:27:53,090 --> 00:27:56,550
No. I'm not worried about you.
I'm worried about Crony.

355
00:27:58,220 --> 00:28:01,310
I'm worried that you'll cause trouble.

356
00:28:01,890 --> 00:28:05,230
Hey. If he loses his mind,
he's worse than most of the thugs here.

357
00:28:05,310 --> 00:28:06,810
Wasn't that in that 100,000 Q&A?

358
00:28:06,900 --> 00:28:09,900
It probably is, but I read only
10 pages so far.

359
00:28:10,480 --> 00:28:12,440
There are 1,000 pages.

360
00:28:14,150 --> 00:28:16,360
And I know Je-hyeok is psychotic.

361
00:28:16,450 --> 00:28:19,330
I saw it myself. I saw him take down
Seagull at the detention center.

362
00:28:22,120 --> 00:28:24,790
I'm also worried about Crony.

363
00:28:24,870 --> 00:28:28,330
He'll get stepped on good this time,
if he acts out.

364
00:28:29,380 --> 00:28:33,800
Then Je-hyeok may have his sentence
extended or get demerits or something.

365
00:28:34,630 --> 00:28:36,970
Don't you worry. I won't cause trouble.

366
00:28:38,550 --> 00:28:40,050
I can finally play baseball again.

367
00:28:40,890 --> 00:28:45,100
I finally got my form back.
Why would I do that? I won't.

368
00:28:46,270 --> 00:28:48,690
Don't you worry. Nothing will happen.

369
00:28:48,770 --> 00:28:51,690
Wow. You have your temper
under so much control now.

370
00:28:52,270 --> 00:28:54,240
How can you not get angry? I can't.

371
00:29:01,080 --> 00:29:02,330
<i>HOLY BIBLE</i>

372
00:29:02,410 --> 00:29:03,240
<i>TALMUD</i>

373
00:29:03,330 --> 00:29:04,250
<i>HEART SUTRA</i>

374
00:29:04,330 --> 00:29:05,160
<i>CAIGENTAN</i>

375
00:29:05,250 --> 00:29:06,080
<i>FORGIVENESS</i>

376
00:29:06,160 --> 00:29:07,160
<i>QURAN</i>

377
00:29:07,250 --> 00:29:08,790
<i>BECOME BROTHERS WITH YOUR ENEMIES</i>

378
00:29:09,630 --> 00:29:12,040
-What is this?
-I'm cultivating my mind.

379
00:29:14,800 --> 00:29:16,010
I'm honing my mind.

380
00:29:19,010 --> 00:29:21,350
I can't ruin my life
because of that bastard.

381
00:29:23,060 --> 00:29:23,970
I'll hold it in.

382
00:29:25,060 --> 00:29:27,100
I'm trying to forgive him.

383
00:29:27,890 --> 00:29:29,730
I'm trying my best
to think only about baseball.

384
00:29:29,810 --> 00:29:31,520
What if he suddenly stabs you?

385
00:29:31,610 --> 00:29:35,150
What if he comes and stabs you
while you're cultivating your mind?

386
00:29:35,820 --> 00:29:38,360
What, would I just sit there
while he comes at me?

387
00:29:40,990 --> 00:29:42,490
I'll try to avoid him.

388
00:29:43,910 --> 00:29:45,330
I won't let him come at me.

389
00:29:47,160 --> 00:29:49,040
It's okay. Nothing will happen.

390
00:29:50,830 --> 00:29:52,290
My cellmates are helping, too.

391
00:29:52,880 --> 00:29:56,210
Oh, my goodness. What a saint.

392
00:30:06,850 --> 00:30:07,680
Gratitude.

393
00:30:09,140 --> 00:30:11,150
No. Courage.

394
00:30:11,980 --> 00:30:14,110
Edelweiss' meaning is "courage."

395
00:30:16,530 --> 00:30:17,570
Have courage.

396
00:30:18,440 --> 00:30:20,610
You'll take the mound again.

397
00:30:21,530 --> 00:30:22,660
Thank you.

398
00:30:27,910 --> 00:30:29,080
What's with them?

399
00:30:30,000 --> 00:30:30,920
No clue.

400
00:30:31,670 --> 00:30:34,210
Min-chul's been exuding estrogen lately.

401
00:30:35,380 --> 00:30:36,550
He's so sappy.

402
00:30:38,920 --> 00:30:39,840
What about that?

403
00:30:40,670 --> 00:30:42,180
Guess what that flower means.

404
00:30:43,010 --> 00:30:44,680
What's its name?

405
00:30:45,300 --> 00:30:47,470
Poppy. Red poppy.

406
00:30:47,890 --> 00:30:48,890
You can grow it.

407
00:30:49,480 --> 00:30:50,680
What does poppy mean?

408
00:30:54,440 --> 00:30:55,480
Looney?

409
00:30:59,780 --> 00:31:01,400
Looney should be okay, right?

410
00:31:02,610 --> 00:31:06,280
Wow. Is he Sleeping Beauty or something?

411
00:31:06,410 --> 00:31:09,700
How many hours is he sleeping?
He does open his eyes, right?

412
00:31:10,120 --> 00:31:12,580
Amazing. Who knew
a person could sleep so much?

413
00:31:12,670 --> 00:31:15,380
He woke up an hour ago and had porridge.

414
00:31:15,960 --> 00:31:16,920
Did you just get here?

415
00:31:17,500 --> 00:31:19,510
Did you come straight here?
The afternoon shift?

416
00:31:20,090 --> 00:31:23,180
Yes. Lieutenant asked me to do something
on his way out.

417
00:31:23,260 --> 00:31:26,720
He said to bring a gift for Looney
for really quitting drugs.

418
00:31:27,390 --> 00:31:29,770
-Here.
-Wow. Ice cream.

419
00:31:29,850 --> 00:31:32,690
That's something you can't have in prison.

420
00:31:32,770 --> 00:31:35,310
But he's sleeping. What should I do?
They'll melt.

421
00:31:35,400 --> 00:31:37,110
What else? We'll eat them all.

422
00:31:43,240 --> 00:31:45,070
Thanks for this.

423
00:31:46,280 --> 00:31:47,120
Enjoy.

424
00:31:47,950 --> 00:31:49,790
I thank you too.

425
00:31:50,370 --> 00:31:52,620
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

426
00:31:54,250 --> 00:31:55,540
Hello.

427
00:31:56,000 --> 00:31:58,920
Hey, Song. What are you doing?

428
00:31:59,500 --> 00:32:00,800
It's time for Wing 2's bath.

429
00:32:01,380 --> 00:32:04,590
They're freaking out
that we're not taking them.

430
00:32:05,180 --> 00:32:06,260
Okay.

431
00:32:07,550 --> 00:32:09,720
-Move quickly.
-Geez.

432
00:32:10,390 --> 00:32:12,520
The poor guy can't even eat his ice cream.

433
00:32:12,600 --> 00:32:13,730
He's quiet when he eats.

434
00:32:15,940 --> 00:32:16,770
Okay, then.

435
00:32:21,480 --> 00:32:23,650
What? Where are you going?

436
00:32:24,240 --> 00:32:25,320
Shower.

437
00:32:26,360 --> 00:32:28,410
I'm not sick at all anymore.

438
00:32:28,780 --> 00:32:30,240
Please let me take a shower.

439
00:32:32,750 --> 00:32:34,370
I want to take a shower.

440
00:32:35,660 --> 00:32:38,000
I'm all better, doctor.

441
00:32:40,500 --> 00:32:42,250
I'll take him.

442
00:32:42,840 --> 00:32:44,380
Just let him go.

443
00:32:44,470 --> 00:32:49,180
Sure. But you have to be careful.
You can't go in hot water yet.

444
00:32:49,260 --> 00:32:52,640
Goodness. It's too hot for hot water.

445
00:32:54,310 --> 00:32:57,980
Hurry up and change.
I'll take you to the shower room.

446
00:33:33,310 --> 00:33:35,770
Seriously, he's so annoying.

447
00:33:38,350 --> 00:33:40,310
What is that? Where did you get it?

448
00:33:41,110 --> 00:33:42,770
Officer Song gave it to me.

449
00:33:46,360 --> 00:33:49,450
He saved his life.
Coffee isn't a big deal.

450
00:33:52,320 --> 00:33:56,410
Why didn't Han-yang stay in the infirmary?
What's so great about showering?

451
00:33:56,500 --> 00:34:00,540
Right? What's so great about showering?
I don't get it.

452
00:34:00,620 --> 00:34:02,880
In light of that, I will pass
on the shower today.

453
00:34:04,210 --> 00:34:05,670
No shower today!

454
00:34:05,750 --> 00:34:07,920
-Please!
-Please, wash up! Please!

455
00:34:08,510 --> 00:34:09,590
Let us live too, please?

456
00:34:10,180 --> 00:34:12,550
Geez. You scared me.

457
00:34:12,640 --> 00:34:15,390
If you don't wash again today,
I'll break your legs.

458
00:34:15,470 --> 00:34:17,560
I'll submit a formal complaint.

459
00:34:17,850 --> 00:34:20,310
Screw you both.

460
00:34:20,480 --> 00:34:22,310
Like you're so clean.

461
00:34:22,860 --> 00:34:24,480
Crony doesn't wash that well either.

462
00:34:24,570 --> 00:34:26,280
I don't care whether or not he...

463
00:34:59,930 --> 00:35:02,480
It's okay. It's okay, Jung-woo.

464
00:35:16,870 --> 00:35:18,370
I need to use the toilet.

465
00:35:18,490 --> 00:35:20,160
Okay. Sure.

466
00:35:25,580 --> 00:35:26,670
Yikes!

467
00:35:31,670 --> 00:35:32,510
Min-chul.

468
00:35:32,590 --> 00:35:35,720
I think I broke my back.

469
00:35:37,300 --> 00:35:38,180
What do I do?

470
00:35:39,100 --> 00:35:40,350
Min-chul, are you okay?

471
00:35:43,640 --> 00:35:44,690
Oh no.

472
00:35:46,310 --> 00:35:47,610
What do we do?

473
00:35:47,690 --> 00:35:50,690
-Slowly. This way. Here.
-No.

474
00:36:03,370 --> 00:36:05,710
Freeze. What are you doing?

475
00:36:17,850 --> 00:36:19,010
I said to stop!

476
00:36:19,430 --> 00:36:21,430
What do you take me for? Get over here!

477
00:36:31,360 --> 00:36:32,440
Shit.

478
00:36:34,490 --> 00:36:37,240
SEOBU PENITENTIARY

479
00:36:40,330 --> 00:36:42,450
Nice! Good job, Je-hyeok.

480
00:36:43,040 --> 00:36:44,580
His speed and control improved a lot.

481
00:36:44,660 --> 00:36:47,210
He should be able to face
a batter or two with that.

482
00:36:47,290 --> 00:36:51,000
That's right. He's capable of
at least a one-point relief.

483
00:36:51,920 --> 00:36:54,050
If lucky, if he can do more,

484
00:36:54,630 --> 00:36:56,380
he may be a middle reliever.

485
00:37:05,980 --> 00:37:08,310
He almost made it into the major league,
but now...

486
00:37:09,650 --> 00:37:10,940
hopes to be a middle relief.

487
00:37:35,260 --> 00:37:36,800
-Lieutenant Lee.
-Yes?

488
00:37:37,380 --> 00:37:40,260
Can you do the night inspections
for my wing tonight?

489
00:37:40,340 --> 00:37:42,390
I need to go to the hospital.

490
00:37:42,850 --> 00:37:44,180
Are you sick?

491
00:37:44,310 --> 00:37:46,810
No. I have a medical checkup today.

492
00:37:47,390 --> 00:37:49,850
Why don't you ask Lieutenant Paeng?

493
00:37:49,940 --> 00:37:51,520
He worked two nights in a row.

494
00:37:51,610 --> 00:37:53,610
You can't call him, okay?

495
00:37:54,110 --> 00:37:56,030
-Fine.
-Thank you.

496
00:37:57,030 --> 00:37:58,110
Oh yeah, Lieutenant Lee.

497
00:37:58,200 --> 00:38:00,910
I heard reporters are calling
Je-hyeok Kim for interviews.

498
00:38:00,990 --> 00:38:03,120
Shouldn't you become his manager as well?

499
00:38:03,910 --> 00:38:05,370
Why is he suddenly doing interviews?

500
00:38:06,290 --> 00:38:08,080
-There was that article.
-What?

501
00:38:08,210 --> 00:38:09,670
Why is he suddenly doing interviews?

502
00:38:10,590 --> 00:38:12,380
-There was that article.
-What?

503
00:38:12,460 --> 00:38:16,090
Didn't you know? It just came out that
Je-hyeok Kim is playing baseball again.

504
00:38:16,180 --> 00:38:19,350
That he changed his throwing arm to right,
and that he's doing rehab in prison.

505
00:38:19,930 --> 00:38:23,140
The Internet's buzzing about that.
Je-hyeok is most trending.

506
00:38:24,270 --> 00:38:27,520
I bet the warden was really disappointed.

507
00:38:27,600 --> 00:38:30,690
He was saving that
for his favorite reporter Mr. Yong.

508
00:38:31,270 --> 00:38:32,980
How did that get out?

509
00:38:33,070 --> 00:38:36,530
True. There are so many people here.
It's surprising it didn't...

510
00:38:39,070 --> 00:38:40,490
Do the inspection for me.

511
00:38:41,580 --> 00:38:43,700
-I heard.
-How?

512
00:38:43,790 --> 00:38:45,830
Min-chul sent me a message.

513
00:38:47,000 --> 00:38:49,670
What do I do? The warden will flip out.

514
00:38:49,750 --> 00:38:51,840
That was my first concern too.

515
00:38:52,840 --> 00:38:56,510
We can worry about him later.
So? Will you do the interviews?

516
00:38:56,590 --> 00:38:58,220
An inmate can't do interviews.

517
00:38:58,800 --> 00:39:00,090
I should know my place.

518
