01:22:45,760 --> 01:22:48,430
Je-hyeok. Stop it.

1041
01:22:48,520 --> 01:22:49,940
That's enough!

1042
01:22:50,480 --> 01:22:51,980
-Hey!
-This bastard needs more beating.

1043
01:22:52,060 --> 01:22:54,560
-Stop it.
-He's still fine! You shit!

1044
01:22:54,770 --> 01:22:56,270
Stop acting, asshole!

1045
01:22:56,860 --> 01:22:58,570
-Je-hyeok, please!
-Let go!

1046
01:22:58,650 --> 01:23:00,740
-Stop it!
-I'm going to kill this bastard.

1047
01:23:01,400 --> 01:23:04,120
-I'll kill this asshole!
-Stop!

1048
01:23:05,530 --> 01:23:06,870
Hey. Je-hyeok.

1049
01:23:07,410 --> 01:23:09,750
-Stop it!
-Asshole. Get over here.

1050
01:23:10,250 --> 01:23:11,830
<i>A broadcast shared with 50,000 inmates.</i>

1051
01:23:11,920 --> 01:23:14,880
<i>I am Min-joo Lee, your host
of the Borami Broadcast.</i>

1052
01:23:15,210 --> 01:23:17,340
<i>It's the hottest day of the summer.</i>

1053
01:23:17,420 --> 01:23:21,420
<i>In Gyeongju, Gyeongsang Province,
temperatures reached 40°C.</i>

1054
01:23:22,010 --> 01:23:24,470
<i>Even pro baseball had to take the day off.</i>

1055
01:23:24,720 --> 01:23:26,050
<i>Tomorrow,</i>

1056
01:23:26,140 --> 01:23:29,560
<i>the 2017 Pro Baseball All-Star Game
will be held in Gocheok Dome.</i>

1057
01:23:29,640 --> 01:23:32,230
<i>-The stadium is surrounded...</i>
-It's so hot.

1058
01:23:32,310 --> 01:23:34,900
<i>with people trying to get tickets.</i>

1059
01:23:34,980 --> 01:23:38,690
Lieutenant Paeng.
What's the cafeteria serving for dinner?

1060
01:23:38,780 --> 01:23:40,030
Kimchi fried rice.

1061
01:23:40,110 --> 01:23:43,990
It's summer. Can't they make
cold noodles or something?

1062
01:23:45,870 --> 01:23:46,950
Does it taste good?

1063
01:23:49,330 --> 01:23:50,950
Well, it's just...

1064
01:23:52,370 --> 01:23:54,000
Long sleeves and a fan in the summer...

1065
01:23:59,880 --> 01:24:01,420
The air conditioner...

1066
01:24:01,510 --> 01:24:03,760
<i>Gocheok Dome means Nexen Heroes,</i>

1067
01:24:03,840 --> 01:24:07,550
<i>and "Nexen Heroes"
reminds you of this player, right?</i>

1068
01:24:07,640 --> 01:24:12,140
<i>Je-hyeok Kim, who is serving his time
diligently and faithfully,</i>

1069
01:24:12,230 --> 01:24:13,640
<i>at Seobu Penitentiary.</i>

1070
01:24:13,980 --> 01:24:16,690
<i>Je-hyeok Kim, are you listening?</i>

1071
01:24:18,480 --> 01:24:19,690
Of course.

1072
01:24:19,770 --> 01:24:23,530
<i>I'd like to send Je-hyeok Kim
and the other 50,000 inmates</i>

1073
01:24:23,610 --> 01:24:26,660
<i>a song of encouragement
for the last song today.</i>

1074
01:24:26,910 --> 01:24:29,870
<i>I hope all of your lives
will be like this.</i>

1075
01:24:29,950 --> 01:24:31,450
<i>"Bravo My Life."</i>

1076
01:24:46,760 --> 01:24:47,590
Knock, knock.

1077
01:24:49,680 --> 01:24:52,020
Are you the Hulk? Put on a shirt.

1078
01:24:52,600 --> 01:24:53,560
I don't have one.

1079
01:25:05,700 --> 01:25:07,950
You didn't eat yet, did you?

1080
01:25:08,030 --> 01:25:09,910
Lieutenant Paeng
brought me kimchi fried rice.

1081
01:25:13,910 --> 01:25:16,670
Joon-ho, I won't be here for life, will I?

1082
01:25:17,370 --> 01:25:18,290
Why you...

1083
01:25:20,210 --> 01:25:22,750
That little... How can you laugh?

1084
01:25:26,930 --> 01:25:29,010
Since Crony instigated it,

1085
01:25:29,220 --> 01:25:31,010
that will be considered.

1086
01:25:31,850 --> 01:25:35,770
And luckily, the guard from the shower
testified nicely for you.

1087
01:25:36,430 --> 01:25:40,270
His testimony was very favorable
toward you.

1088
01:25:41,940 --> 01:25:43,360
He's good-looking too.

1089
01:25:49,910 --> 01:25:50,990
You freaking psycho.

1090
01:25:52,450 --> 01:25:54,490
You almost killed Crony.

1091
01:25:55,080 --> 01:25:58,460
You were almost going to rot in prison
for the rest of your life!

1092
01:25:59,580 --> 01:26:00,540
You crazy freak.

1093
01:26:02,380 --> 01:26:03,960
Do you think I'm that stupid?

1094
01:26:05,420 --> 01:26:06,800
I knew you were there.

1095
01:26:10,590 --> 01:26:11,470
Thanks.

1096
01:26:14,470 --> 01:26:15,770
I mean it. Thanks.

1097
01:26:16,980 --> 01:26:18,310
Whatever.

1098
01:26:22,810 --> 01:26:24,520
<i>Access granted.</i>

1099
01:26:25,530 --> 01:26:28,990
Why would you ruin your life
because of a scumbag like that?

1100
01:26:29,070 --> 01:26:30,780
You almost hurt your right hand,

1101
01:26:30,860 --> 01:26:32,740
extended your sentence,
and killed your career.

1102
01:26:32,820 --> 01:26:35,540
Those scumbags aren't even worth hitting.

1103
01:26:36,620 --> 01:26:39,290
Anyway, you can be at peace
for the next few days.

1104
01:26:39,370 --> 01:26:43,920
Crony is in the hospital until next week.
Don't worry until then.

1105
01:26:44,000 --> 01:26:46,590
Right hand. You must get it treated.

1106
01:26:46,800 --> 01:26:48,880
Oh, my. So, you like flowers.

1107
01:26:51,550 --> 01:26:53,760
Leave. I'll take Je-hyeok Kim
to the infirmary.

1108
01:26:54,680 --> 01:26:57,930
He's my inmate from my wing.
Please stick to the rules.

1109
01:26:58,520 --> 01:27:00,730
When? This Saturday? Endoscopy?

1110
01:27:06,780 --> 01:27:08,190
Must I really do this?

1111
01:27:09,190 --> 01:27:11,780
Can't a fan do that for his star?

1112
01:27:12,700 --> 01:27:15,240
Are you sure that's wild rose?

1113
01:27:15,330 --> 01:27:18,080
Yes. The greenhouse gave it to me.
Whom is it for?

1114
01:27:21,000 --> 01:27:22,000
Let's go.

1115
01:27:22,080 --> 01:27:25,460
Like this. Okay. Good, good.

1116
01:27:25,540 --> 01:27:28,590
You must've hit him properly.

1117
01:27:29,170 --> 01:27:31,590
Still, you should always be careful.
Let me see.

1118
01:27:36,430 --> 01:27:39,560
-Can we talk outside...
-What? Me?

1119
01:27:40,140 --> 01:27:42,100
Why? Are you hurt?

1120
01:27:42,190 --> 01:27:43,480
Well, everything aches...

1121
01:27:44,060 --> 01:27:46,650
Gosh. It's because
you don't exercise enough.

1122
01:27:46,730 --> 01:27:49,150
You can't hurt your back.
You're not even married.

1123
01:28:06,330 --> 01:28:08,630
Why don't you want to live?

1124
01:28:11,010 --> 01:28:13,430
It's so discouraging to the person
who saved you.

1125
01:28:20,560 --> 01:28:22,730
I heard from Min-chul

1126
01:28:24,060 --> 01:28:25,150
about your daughter...

1127
01:28:26,480 --> 01:28:27,360
and wife.

1128
01:28:33,780 --> 01:28:35,700
Do you think your daughter would be happy

1129
01:28:36,360 --> 01:28:37,820
to see you like this?

1130
01:28:49,090 --> 01:28:50,500
It's wild rose.

1131
01:29:00,600 --> 01:29:02,100
This flower means...

1132
01:29:08,610 --> 01:29:10,110
"I miss

1133
01:29:11,980 --> 01:29:13,570
the cottage on a hill

1134
01:29:17,320 --> 01:29:20,660
in my home country down south,

1135
01:29:21,700 --> 01:29:23,870
where wild roses bloom."

1136
01:29:24,700 --> 01:29:26,080
Isn't that a song?

1137
01:29:28,370 --> 01:29:29,380
How did you know?

1138
01:29:36,260 --> 01:29:37,800
Okay, then.

1139
01:29:48,730 --> 01:29:50,310
<i>What does poppy mean?</i>

1140
01:29:51,270 --> 01:29:52,360
Looney?

1141
01:29:56,860 --> 01:29:58,150
Looney should be okay, right?

1142
01:30:02,280 --> 01:30:03,410
What is this flower?

1143
01:30:05,290 --> 01:30:07,120
-It's wild rose.
-I see.

1144
01:30:08,500 --> 01:30:11,250
Wild rose means...

1145
01:30:15,590 --> 01:30:17,880
"Solitude, cautious love."

1146
01:30:19,220 --> 01:30:20,430
And...

1147
01:30:23,180 --> 01:30:24,430
"Longing for family."

1148
01:30:28,520 --> 01:30:30,100
Do you want to take it?

1149
01:30:31,020 --> 01:30:32,400
No, thank you.

1150
01:30:33,560 --> 01:30:34,650
I'll look at it here.

1151
01:30:37,190 --> 01:30:38,740
It's pretty.

1152
01:30:46,790 --> 01:30:48,080
<i>RECONCILIATION
FORGIVENESS</i>

1153
01:30:48,870 --> 01:30:50,080
Are you throwing these away?

1154
01:30:51,210 --> 01:30:52,540
Yeah, throw them out.

1155
01:30:54,170 --> 01:30:55,710
Je-hyeok, what's your sign?

1156
01:30:55,800 --> 01:30:57,260
I'm a rabbit.

1157
01:30:59,420 --> 01:31:01,760
Let's see.

1158
01:31:02,140 --> 01:31:04,970
"What you want desperately will happen,

1159
01:31:05,890 --> 01:31:07,810
and you'll receive good news"?

1160
01:31:08,390 --> 01:31:10,100
Good news? A woman?

1161
01:31:11,850 --> 01:31:13,230
Good news for Je-hyeok would be...

1162
01:31:17,320 --> 01:31:18,570
Je-hyeok, visitation.

1163
01:31:19,360 --> 01:31:20,190
It's your attorney.

1164
01:31:35,670 --> 01:31:36,500
Je-hyeok.

1165
01:31:37,880 --> 01:31:38,840
Are you ready?

1166
01:31:40,630 --> 01:31:43,220
Just tell me. I'm fine.

1167
01:31:44,010 --> 01:31:45,640
Good news, bad news,

1168
01:31:47,010 --> 01:31:48,310
I'm ready for both.

1169
01:31:52,310 --> 01:31:56,400
I called all ten teams
after coming to see you,

1170
01:31:56,770 --> 01:31:57,980
and I met with them all.

1171
01:32:02,950 --> 01:32:04,030
All ten teams...

1172
01:32:09,080 --> 01:32:10,660
want to sign you.

1173
01:32:13,410 --> 01:32:14,920
Even Nexen.

1174
01:32:23,420 --> 01:32:24,680
You did well, Je-hyeok.

1175
01:32:32,100 --> 01:32:33,890
Let's start over

1176
01:32:35,100 --> 01:32:36,650
like when we first met.

1177
01:32:52,910 --> 01:32:53,960
<i>Je-hyeok?</i>

1178
01:32:55,210 --> 01:32:56,500
<i>It's you, isn't it?</i>

1179
01:32:59,840 --> 01:33:02,630
If you were going to call like this,
why did you break up with me?

1180
01:33:04,260 --> 01:33:07,180
We broke up. Wake up.

1181
01:34:02,230 --> 01:34:04,280
<i>Where is our Je-hyeok Kim going?</i>

1182
01:34:04,940 --> 01:34:05,820
<i>On what terms?</i>

1183
01:34:05,900 --> 01:34:08,240
Hey, Je-hyeok Kim!
Buy dinner once you sign with a team.

1184
01:34:08,990 --> 01:34:12,070
-Good luck.
-You didn't even sign yet.

1185
01:34:12,160 --> 01:34:13,370
<i>Are there any terms you want?</i>

1186
01:34:13,450 --> 01:34:15,500
Want me to bury Je-hyeok Kim for you?

1187
01:34:16,080 --> 01:34:19,120
He went through so much, and was wronged.

1188
01:34:19,210 --> 01:34:21,040
<i>He can say that much.</i>

1189
01:34:21,130 --> 01:34:22,170
<i>Je-hyeok.</i>

1190
01:34:25,880 --> 01:34:28,010
-What happened to his hair?
-Han-yang...

1191
01:34:28,090 --> 01:34:30,720
<i>Looney's cute.
Why do you hate him so much?</i>

1192
01:34:30,800 --> 01:34:34,100
-Just get treated, bastard.
-I am, bastard.

1193
01:34:36,470 --> 01:34:37,980
<i>-In the summer
-Aren't you hot?</i>

1194
01:34:38,060 --> 01:34:39,190
I'm cold.

1195
01:34:39,270 --> 01:34:42,440
<i>It's withdrawal. Please understand.</i>

1196
01:34:42,940 --> 01:34:46,230
<i>Jung-woo, help him out. You're friends.</i>

1197
01:34:46,320 --> 01:34:47,570
You'll be there, right?

1198
01:34:47,650 --> 01:34:49,650
If you quit. It's up to you.

1199
01:34:49,740 --> 01:34:52,160
<i>Is he really trying to quit?
It'll be impossible.</i>

1200
01:34:52,240 --> 01:34:54,990
<i>He's being treated and stuff too,
so he'll be cured.</i>

1201
01:34:55,490 --> 01:34:57,500
<i>To be honest, I'm not sure.</i>

1202
01:34:58,870 --> 01:35:02,710
<i>He neglects his duties,
jokes around with the inmates...</i>

1203
01:35:02,790 --> 01:35:05,090
<i>Lieutenant Paeng is delinquent
and emotional.</i>

1204
01:35:05,170 --> 01:35:08,300
<i>Hey, Kang! What's that smoke in Wing 5A?</i>

1205
01:35:08,380 --> 01:35:10,010
<i>Lieutenant! Fire!</i>

1206
01:35:10,090 --> 01:35:13,090
<i>Fire. Fire. A fire has broken out.</i>

1207
01:35:13,680 --> 01:35:17,310
<i>Please follow the guards' instructions
and escape quickly.</i>

1208
01:35:17,430 --> 01:35:20,230
<i>Over 50 inmates died,
and there were numerous injured.</i>

1209
01:35:20,810 --> 01:35:23,940
-What are you doing?
<i>-He finally caused trouble.</i>

1210
01:35:24,020 --> 01:35:25,650
<i>Transfer Lieutenant Paeng elsewhere.</i>

